<subSubSection id="C3536B9EE951FF894B3FFE15FAFDFAEF" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BF63815E951FF894B3FFE15FAE4FD81" blockId="5.[826,1441,405,580]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis id="B93DE407E951FF894B3FFE15FC22FE6E" box="[826,945,406,427]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Dorsoventrally compressed 
<taxonomicName id="4C494396E951FF894D0FFE16FCF9FE0F" authorityName="POCHE" authorityYear="1913" class="Cyrtophoria" family="Hartmannulidae" kingdom="Protozoa" order="Cyrtophorida" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="family">Hartmannulidae</taxonomicName>
with a podite; oral kineties reduced to two fragments; several kinetal fragments positioned on the right posterior of frontoventral kineties; postoral kineties strongly shortened posteriad; terminal fragments consisting of several parallel arranged fragments.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF63815E951FF894B3FFDEDFC13FD04" blockId="5.[826,1441,622,705]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis id="B93DE407E951FF894B3FFDEDFC43FD46" box="[826,976,622,643]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<typeStatus id="54F286B7E951FF894B3FFDEDFCFDFD46" box="[826,878,622,643]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Type</typeStatus>
species:
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C494396E951FF894BDBFDEDFA32FD41" authority="(Deroux, 1976)" authorityName="Pan &amp; Lin &amp; Gong &amp; Al-Rashied &amp; Song" authorityYear="2012" baseAuthorityName="Deroux" baseAuthorityYear="1976" box="[990,1441,622,644]" class="Cyrtophoria" family="Hartmannulidae" genus="Aporthotrochilia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Cyrtophorida" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="species" species="pulex" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="B93DE407E951FF894BDBFDEDFB77FD46" box="[990,1252,622,643]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Aporthotrochilia pulex</emphasis>
(Deroux, 1976)
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A20E597CE951FF894B3FFD0FFC24FD67" box="[826,951,652,674]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(basionym: 
<taxonomicName id="4C494396E951FF894C48FD0FFCE7FD04" authority="Deroux, 1976" authorityName="Deroux" authorityYear="1976" class="Cyrtophoria" family="Hartmannulidae" genus="Trichopodiella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Cyrtophorida" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="species" species="pulex">
<emphasis id="B93DE407E951FF894C48FD0FFAA9FD64" box="[1101,1338,652,673]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Trichopodiella pulex</emphasis>
Deroux, 1976
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF63815E951FF894B3FFD68FC1DFCFB" blockId="5.[826,1441,747,830]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis id="B93DE407E951FF894B3FFD68FC2BFCC5" box="[826,952,747,768]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Etymology:</emphasis>
Composite of Greek prefix apo- (derived from) and the generic name 
<taxonomicName id="4C494396E951FF894C8CFC8AFABFFCDB" authorityName="Song" authorityYear="2003" box="[1161,1324,777,798]" class="Cyrtophoria" family="Aegyrianidae" genus="Orthotrochilia" kingdom="Protozoa" order="Dysteriida" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93DE407E951FF894C8CFC8AFABFFCDB" box="[1161,1324,777,798]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Orthotrochilia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; feminine gender.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF63815E951FF894B3FFCEBFA9FFB91" blockId="5.[826,1442,872,1322]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis id="B93DE407E951FF894B3FFCEBFC58FCB8" box="[826,971,872,893]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Comparison:</emphasis>
In general, 
<taxonomicName id="4C494396E951FF894C69FCEBFAB4FCB8" authority="Pan &amp; Lin &amp; Gong &amp; Al-Rashied &amp; Song, 2012" authorityName="Pan &amp; Lin &amp; Gong &amp; Al-Rashied &amp; Song" authorityYear="2012" box="[1132,1319,872,893]" class="Cyrtophoria" family="Hartmannulidae" genus="Aporthotrochilia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Cyrtophorida" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="B93DE407E951FF894C69FCEBFAB4FCB8" box="[1132,1319,872,893]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Aporthotrochilia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A20E597CE951FF894D33FCEBFA31FCB8" box="[1334,1442,872,893]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
resembles 
<taxonomicName id="4C494396E951FF894BB3FC05FB72FC5E" authority="Song, 2003" authorityName="Song" authorityYear="2003" box="[950,1249,902,923]" class="Cyrtophoria" family="Aegyrianidae" genus="Orthotrochilia" kingdom="Protozoa" order="Dysteriida" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93DE407E951FF894BB3FC05FBCAFC5E" box="[950,1113,902,923]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Orthotrochilia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFD845E4E951FF894C67FC05FB72FC5E" author="Song W" box="[1122,1249,902,923]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="169 - 177" refId="ref11208" refString="Song W. 2003. On two marine cyrtophorid ciliates from China, with description of Chlamydonella derouxi nov. spec. and Orthotrochilia pilula (Deroux, 1976) nov. comb., and reestablishment of the genus Orthotrochilia nov. gen. (Protozoa, Ciliophora, Cyrtophorida). Hydrobiologia 499: 169 - 177." type="journal article" year="2003">
Song, 
<quantity id="4CB195F0E951FF894CAFFC05FB72FC5E" box="[1194,1249,902,923]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.087619999999999" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" unit="in" value="2003.0">2003</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in oral ciliature and the pattern of postoral kineties. However, the new genus can be distinguished by the presence of several extra kinetal fragments, i.e. the posterior fragments are on right posterior of frontoventral kineties and the higher number of terminal fragments (more than one vs. single) (
<bibRefCitation id="EFD845E4E951FF894C78FBBDFA92FB91" author="Song W" box="[1149,1281,1086,1108]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="169 - 177" refId="ref11208" refString="Song W. 2003. On two marine cyrtophorid ciliates from China, with description of Chlamydonella derouxi nov. spec. and Orthotrochilia pilula (Deroux, 1976) nov. comb., and reestablishment of the genus Orthotrochilia nov. gen. (Protozoa, Ciliophora, Cyrtophorida). Hydrobiologia 499: 169 - 177." type="journal article" year="2003">Song, 2003</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF63815E951FF894B56FBDFFAFDFAEF" blockId="5.[826,1442,872,1322]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
Compared with other closely related genera (e.g. 
<taxonomicName id="4C494396E951FF894B3FFBFFFC50FB54" authorityName="Deroux" authorityYear="1976" box="[826,963,1148,1169]" class="Cyrtophoria" family="Hartmannulidae" genus="Microxysma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Cyrtophorida" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93DE407E951FF894B3FFBFFFC50FB54" box="[826,963,1148,1169]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Microxysma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C494396E951FF894BCAFBF8FBF2FB55" box="[975,1121,1147,1168]" class="Cyrtophoria" family="Trochiliidae" genus="Trochilioides" kingdom="Protozoa" order="Cyrtophorida" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93DE407E951FF894BCAFBF8FBF2FB55" box="[975,1121,1147,1168]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Trochilioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C494396E951FF894C68FBF8FA9AFB55" authorityName="Deroux" authorityYear="1976" box="[1133,1289,1147,1168]" class="Ciliophora (awaiting allocation)" family="Ciliophora (awaiting allocation)" genus="Chlamydonyx" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Ciliophora (awaiting allocation)" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93DE407E951FF894C68FBF8FA9AFB55" box="[1133,1289,1147,1168]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Chlamydonyx</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), 
<taxonomicName id="4C494396E951FF894D1BFBF8FCE8FB6A" authorityName="Pan &amp; Lin &amp; Gong &amp; Al-Rashied &amp; Song" authorityYear="2012" class="Cyrtophoria" family="Hartmannulidae" genus="Aporthotrochilia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Cyrtophorida" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93DE407E951FF894D1BFBF8FCE8FB6A" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Aporthotrochilia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be clearly identified by having two perioral kineties (vs. two circumoral and one preoral kineties), several terminal fragments (vs. single), and several extra kinety fragments caudally positioned on right of frontoventral kineties (vs. none) (
<bibRefCitation id="EFD845E4E951FF894CBEFA97FAF0FAEF" author="Deroux G" box="[1211,1379,1300,1322]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="505 - 538" refId="ref9141" refString="Deroux G. 1976 c. Plan cortical des Cyrtophorida. III. - Les structures differenciatrices chez les Dysteriina. Protistologica 12: 505 - 538." type="journal article" year="1976">Deroux, 1976c</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
